						"title": "Minimize risks and complexity of agentic AI adoption",
						"subtitle": "Balance the need for security and speed",
						"copy": "Organizations are racing to launch AI agents. In fact, 95% of companies plan to adopt agentic AI even faster than GenAI.* \n\nBut adopting agents too quickly can introduce risks, costs, and complexity that stall innovation instead of fueling it. \n\nThis creates a dilemma for organizations that need to balance the speed of adoption with security and scale. \n\nThis position paper looks at three key considerations when adopting agentic AI, including:\n\n- Why thinking globally is a must for a fast, reliable user experience\n- How compute pricing model flexibility helps scale up and down\n- Ways to prioritize integration and efficiency for security services\n",
